HEADWORD: Gomer
<hw>Go"mer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A Hebrew measure. See
<er>Homer</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gomer</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Gomer
<hw>Go"mer</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Gun.)</fld> <def>A conical chamber
at the breech of the bore in heavy ordnance, especially in mortars; --
named after the inventor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gommelin</ent>⟦br⟧
